spanGrp.span: We take care of the chickens ourselves;
Sa t shkoro senw-g sa wakwa t
we breed them ourselves, and we raise them.
shkoro tseginw-g je kebiw-g sa wakwa t
So, they have grown and ready to be eaten,
Jekepa sa shkoro dega-ka keyge kata-n bi
shkoro pupu je te-g-w sa t
and we boil water in a big pot.
Sa t digl baw-g olla n keyge bw
When it is really hot and boiling
we put in the chicken we killed to cook its feathers;
Jen kepa sa t mn shkoro t-w jw-g-m eli-n k eli-n-s'
then we pluck it totally and clean it well.
kepa sa t klabe kye-g-m k mnram k
We then burn it on the fire
Jekepa sa t padlw-g-n yuk inga n
and cut it according to its own skeleton.
jekepa sa t wti-g k mn mn wjie-l bi
when it is well-cooked and tender,
we add chopped plantains, manioc, pumpkin, and mirliton.
Je ra sa t chom bi r shk bi r ke jarw bi r pis bil je wbige-g-n jnmn jrga ra
Jrga sa t ke mn jir ts jn bi jaw-g-n n
Thats how it gets its flavor;
wa/ je ra kei ta r ta
if you dont add anything it wont taste good.
ka jir j-n n ra ka kei ta
Jekepa jebi eliw-g sa t r
that is our chicken; according to us,
Je r sa (_) shkoro sa sa wakwara je n
that is the one that really tastes good.
je n r kei ta bi r
But the one that the people down there [the whites] have no taste at all.
ta dia pe t watu-g bi je ka kei ta yess
We cook the chicken like that;
then we sit down with our children
jekepa sa sa jgl-g-w-n sa yabla ra
and our relatives and eat it.
